0.Instruction: Prepare a bowl in front of you at about chest height.

1.Instruction: Position the bowl a little bit more on the right side.

2.Instruction: Take the lighter weight object, the cube.

3.Instruction: Pick up the cube and try to lift it as much as you can.

4.Instruction: Bend your arm as much as the brace will allow as you move the cube.

5.Instruction: Move the cube to your right.

6.Instruction: Place the cube on the side of the table and gently let it go.

7.Instruction: Lower your hand and pick up the banana.

8.Instruction: Lift your arm to bring the banana up towards your face, bending your elbow as much as the brace will allow.

9.Instruction: If the object is too heavy, move your arm out horizontally instead of lifting the banana high.

10.Instruction: Place the banana gently on the table.

11.Instruction: Grab the last cube in the bowl and try to lift it a little bit higher if possible.

12.Instruction: Move the cube to your side and then gently set it down.
